message: Continue to add sources, including an Illinois Historical Society source that hopefully settles the issue of pronouns.

/* Enlistment */ Corrected age at enlistment to conform with birth date; nothing in cited source suggests Cashier represented his age to be 17, believe this was human error at time of writing this article.
Added additional citations supporting the fact that Cashier properly is identified as a transgender man, and therefore that the "he/his/him" pronouns are appropriate.

Edited to acknowledge that Albert Cashier was, in fact, a trans man. It is unthinkable that a wikipedia would use female pronouns when Cashier plainly identified with as a male; while he was biologically born female, that means nothing in terms of gender.
